thread.title: Warren Hills' Shane Deemer is Week 6 New Jersey MVP
thread.title_full: Warren Hills' Shane Deemer is Week 6 New Jersey MVP

title: Warren Hills' Shane Deemer is Week 6 New Jersey MVP
text:
Warren Hills' Shane Deemer runs away from North Plainfield's Arthur Gilmore last Friday. (lehighvalleylive.com file photo) By Tom Hinkel | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 13, 2015 9:00 AM 
lehighvalleylive Week 6 New Jersey Football Most Valuable Player Shane Deemer (lehighvalleylive.com file photo) 
Shane Deemer , Warren Hills 
The senior running back/linebacker broke loose for 188 yards and two touchdowns on 15 carries in a 27-6 victory over North Plainfield. It was the Blue Streaks' first game since senior quarterback Evan Murray died from a lacerated spleen he suffered while playing against Summit on Sept. 25. 
Deemer had touchdown runs of 35 and 46 yards in the second quarter to help stake the Blue Streaks to a 21-0 halftime lead. 
Check out the high school football page for more Players of the Week and full coverage.
